I like King's use of Byron's symbolism in &quot;Childe Harold to the
Dark Tower Came.&quot; Evidently King's Dark Tower series is a
contemporary quest analog of sorts, featuring The Gunfighter, but
indepentently of characters. Anyone who searches for Lord Byron
&quot;Dark Tower,&quot; as I just did, can estimate its contemporary vogue
and academic interests. The use of the supernatural in
literature has a distinguished Gothic history, and now they speak
of its use in an anti-civilization genre, with H. P. Lovecraft
and T. S. Eliot as exponents.

I would give King an even chance of winning the Nobel Prize for
Literature.

