Note that it's not the presence of any particular cliche that's a real
problem, it's the ratio of cliches in each paragraph to felicitous phrases
(none) and/or striking images (none). It would be tough for King to
come up with a striking image anyway because he's constantly using
what I call vague-osities, some indeterminate phrase like &quot;halfway across&quot;,
or &quot;small amount of&quot;.

As for Bookburn's comments concerning the Dark Tower series and Byron
and the Nobel prize...I guess she's pulling my leg. I skimmed through part
four and not only was there not anything of even slight interest, it was also
a hilariously tasteless compilation of butt-sniffing and urination scenes.
I honestly have no idea what anybody sees in this crap.

